The police in Limpopo arrested a possible vehicle theft syndicate at a village in Ha-Mashau, outside Makhado, found in a position of trucks worth an estimated value of R24 million on Sunday. The police said this came during efforts to deal with the theft of motor vehicles and incidences of cross-border crimes in Limpopo through a joint operation on Sunday. “A sting of operation was conducted after a tip-off from members of the community on a motor vehicle syndicate which is operating from various provinces. In the process of following the tracks of this syndicate, a 37-year-old man was arrested for the possession of suspected stolen vehicles at Mashau Thenga village,” the police said in a statement. During the arrest, five tipper trucks and three water tank trucks were recovered. The police suspect that the trucks were stolen from other provinces and were destined to be smuggled out of the country. The suspects are expected to make a court appearance soon. -TNA Reporter